; nl-neutral-trace-live.fk — THE single command for a legible NL->neutral->NL
; query trace with rag concept match, choice paths, per-rule BMF counters,
; sizes, the three-tongue pivot, the teaching frame, and the north-star map:
;
;     ./fkwu --src cognition/tests/nl-neutral-trace-live.fk
;
; Default lanes: de "Wasser" and id "air", plus the de/en/id pivot exemplar.
; Your own query: stage "<asserted-locale> <target-locale> <query text>" at
; .coherence-network/nl-neutral-trace-query.txt and re-run the same command.
; To score a local/remote oracle against the native answer, stage its answer
; at .coherence-network/nl-neutral-trace-oracle-answer.txt.
;
; Expected loud line: ONE [unresolved-call] (form-ontology-loader.fk's
; walk_recipe_here, kept loud there on purpose). See nl-neutral-trace.fk.
;
; preludes: form/form-stdlib/core.fk form/form-stdlib/str-byte-at.fk form/form-stdlib/string-byte-fold-src-shim.fk form/form-stdlib/record-src-shim.fk
